{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/00003-week1-100-days-of-flutter/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"erluxman","author":"Laxman Bhattarai"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1df3f1c9-940a-54c5-aac1-1d167d3579e2","html":"<h2 id=\"day1-stless--stful\"><a href=\"#day1-stless--stful\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day1 <code class=\"language-text\">stless</code> &#x26; <code class=\"language-text\">stful</code></h2>\n<p>We can type <code class=\"language-text\">stless</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">stful</code> and we get Autocomplete Suggestion to generate Stateless Flutter Widget or Stateful Flutter Widget Respectively.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/01stlesstful.gif\" alt=\"statful\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"day2-if-null-operator-\"><a href=\"#day2-if-null-operator-\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day2 <code class=\"language-text\">If Null</code> Operator (<code class=\"language-text\">??</code>)</h2>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">??</code> checks If something is <code class=\"language-text\">null</code>. If it‚Äôs not null it returns its own value but if it‚Äôs <code class=\"language-text\">null</code> it returns the value after <code class=\"language-text\">??</code></p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">return abc??10; //returns 10 if abc is null else returns its own value,</code></p>\n<p>It also has shorthand assignment when it‚Äôs null.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">abc??=5 //assigns 5 to abc if it&#39;s null</code></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/02ifnull.png\" alt=\"null\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"day3-inner-function\"><a href=\"#day3-inner-function\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day3 Inner Function</h2>\n<p>We can define a function inside another function.</p>\n<p>This is to encapsulate the inner function from everything else outside the outer function.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/03functions.png\" alt=\"functions\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"day4-cascadechainingfluent-api\"><a href=\"#day4-cascadechainingfluent-api\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day4 ..Cascade..Chaining..Fluent API</h2>\n<p>We can chain method/member calls without returning <code class=\"language-text\">this</code> from <strong>method(), getter() and setter()</strong> using cascade operator (..)</p>\n<p>try in <a href=\"https://dartpad.dartlang.org/290e17306b745ed83b9242653ca55041\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Dartpad</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/04cascadebefore.png\" alt=\"cascade\"></p>\n<p>Can be replaced with</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/04cascadeafter.png\" alt=\"cascadeafter\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"day5-dart-data-class\"><a href=\"#day5-dart-data-class\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day5 Dart <code class=\"language-text\">data class</code></h2>\n<p>Dart does not support data class by default, but with plugins, we can simply generate data class (<code class=\"language-text\">copyWith()</code>,<code class=\"language-text\">fromMap()</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">toMap()</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">Named Constructor</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">toString()</code>,<code class=\"language-text\">hashCode()</code> &#x26; <code class=\"language-text\">equals()</code> methods implemented by the tool).</p>\n<h3 id=\"Ô∏ècautionÔ∏è--your-cursor-should-be-inside-the-class-that-you-want-to-generate-data-class\"><a href=\"#%EF%B8%8Fcaution%EF%B8%8F--your-cursor-should-be-inside-the-class-that-you-want-to-generate-data-class\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><code class=\"language-text\">üö®‚ùóÔ∏èCaution‚ùóÔ∏èüö®</code> : <strong>Your cursor should be inside the class that you want to generate data class.</strong></h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/05dataclass.gif\" alt=\"dataclass\"></p>\n<p>Download Plugins :</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/12429-dart-data-class\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">For Android Studio</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=BendixMa.dart-data-class-generator\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">For VsCode</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"day6-richtext-widget\"><a href=\"#day6-richtext-widget\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day6 RichText Widget</h2>\n<p>If you want to have a single text with different style within it? Do not bother or try to hack with with <code class=\"language-text\">Text()</code> and use <code class=\"language-text\">RichText()</code> with <code class=\"language-text\">TextSpan()</code></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://dartpad.dartlang.org/f87dddb2f48f1d1ef0f25903af1ded58\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Try on dartpad</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rykDVh-QFfw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">See Youtube Demo</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/06richtext.png\" alt=\"richtext\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"day7-spacer-widget\"><a href=\"#day7-spacer-widget\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>#Day7 Spacer Widget</h2>\n<p>Using Container with certain height/width to create responsive space between Widgets? That may look good on one screen but will not look the same in different screen size.</p>\n<p>Spacer Widget comes for the rescue. Instead of <code class=\"language-text\">Container(width: / height: )</code>, use <code class=\"language-text\">Spacer(flex: )</code>.</p>\n<p>How on this earth did I not know about this widget earlier? This is going to save many lives üòÇ</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://dartpad.dev/f0d077124527a8078cdb2eede1e9bf73\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Try on dartpad</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7FJgd7QN1zI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">See Youtube Demo</a></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/erluxman/awesomefluttertips/master/assets/07spacer.gif\" alt=\"spacer\"></p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Flutter Tips 1-7","date":"April 11, 2020","spoiler":"First 7 tips and tricks on the series 100DaysOfFlutter.","cta":null},"fields":{"slug":"/00003-week1-100-days-of-flutter/","langKey":"en"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/00003-week1-100-days-of-flutter/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/00002-100-days-of-flutter/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"00002-100-days-of-flutter"},"frontmatter":{"title":"100 Days of Flutter"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/00004-week-2-100days-of-flutter/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"00004-week-2-100days-of-flutter"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Flutter Tips 8-14"}},"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}